# CSS Border Consistency Rules

## üö´ Prohibited Border Patterns
- **NEVER** use `border-left`, `border-right`, `border-top`, or `border-bottom` for highlighting
- **NEVER** use single-side borders for color accents
- **AVOID** inconsistent border styling across components
- **DO NOT** mix border styles within the same component type

## ‚úÖ Required Border Patterns
- **ALWAYS** use full borders (all sides) for all components
- **CONSISTENT** border styling across all similar components
- **UNIFORM** border radius and color application
- **NO EXCEPTIONS** - all borders must be on all four sides

## üé® Standard Border Implementation
```css
/* ‚úÖ CORRECT: Full border with consistent styling */
.data-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}

/* ‚ùå WRONG: Left-only border for highlighting */
.data-card {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-primary);
}

/* ‚úÖ CORRECT: Full border with accent color */
.data-card {
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}

/* ‚ùå WRONG: Any single-side border */
.metric-item {
    border-left: 3px solid #4caf50;
}

/* ‚úÖ CORRECT: Full border on all sides */
.metric-item {
    border: 2px solid #4caf50;
    border-radius: 10px;
}
```

## üéØ Rationale
- **Professional appearance**: Full borders look more polished and complete
- **Consistency**: All components use the same border pattern
- **Accessibility**: Clear visual boundaries improve readability
- **Design coherence**: Unified styling across the application

## üîÑ Border Color Hierarchy
- **Primary borders**: `var(--border-primary)` for main containers
- **Secondary borders**: `var(--border-secondary)` for nested elements
- **Accent borders**: `var(--accent-primary)` for highlighted components
- **Specific colors**: For status indicators (green, red, orange, blue)
- **Consistent application** across all similar components

## üìê Border Width & Radius Standards

### Standard Border Widths
- **Thin borders**: `1px solid` - default for most components
- **Medium borders**: `2px solid` - emphasized components
- **Thick borders**: `3px solid` - use sparingly for high emphasis

### Border Radius Guidelines
- **Small components**: `10px` or `var(--radius-sm)` for cards and containers
- **Medium components**: `20px` or `var(--radius-md)` for larger components
- **Large components**: `30px` or `var(--radius-lg)` for main sections
- **Consistent application** within component types

## üîÑ Migration Pattern
When refactoring existing code with single-side borders:

```css
/* Before (incorrect) */
.element {
    border-left: 4px solid #4caf50;
    padding: 8px 14px;
}

/* After (correct) */
.element {
    border: 2px solid #4caf50;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 10px;
}
```

